  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law intersects with national laws on money laundering through various mechanisms:\n\n1. Global Standards and Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee on Banking Supervision guidelines\n\n2. Legal Cooperation Mechanisms\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing agreements\n- Extradition protocols\n- Cross-border investigations\n\n3. Compliance Requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Customer due diligence procedures\n- International banking transparency standards\n\n4. Enforcement Coordination\n- Interpol investigations\n- Joint law enforcement operations\n- Shared intelligence platforms\n- Coordinated asset seizure and recovery\n\n5. Regulatory Harmonization\n- Standardized definitions of money laundering\n- Consistent legal approaches\n- Aligned penalties and sanctions\n- Uniform reporting requirements\n\n6. International Financial Monitoring\n- Global financial transaction tracking\n- Cross-border transaction surveillance\n- International banking compliance mechanisms\n\nThese intersections create a complex, multilayered approach to combating money laundering through collaborative international legal frameworks.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these specific aspects?",
